<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2015-06-01</DATELINE><TITLE>Molecular Pathogenesis Lessons from the World of Infectious Diseases Research</TITLE><BODY>This Guest Editorial introduces this month's special Infectious Disease Theme Issue, a series of reviews focusing on the molecular pathogenic processes of four representative pathogens, including two bacteria (brucellae and Staphylococcus aureus), a virus (influenza), and a parasite (Trypanosoma cruzi).&#3;</BODY></TEXT>